<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Dendromecon</i> <i>rigida</i>, <i>Eriodictyon</i> <i>californicum</i>, <i>Eriodictyon</i> <i>crassifolium</i>, <i>Eriodictyon</i> <i>parryi</i>, <i>Lotus</i> <i>scoparius</i> and/or <i>Lupinus</i> <i>albifrons</i> is dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Adenostoma</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Artemisia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Baccharis</i> <i>pilularis</i>, <i>Ceanothus</i> <i>cuneatus</i>, <i>Ceanothus</i> <i>greggii</i>, <i>Corethrogyne</i> <i>filaginifolia</i>, <i>Dicentra</i> <i>chrysantha</i>, <i>Diplacus</i> <i>aurantiacus</i>, <i>Ephedra</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Ericameria</i> <i>linearifolia</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Eriophyllum</i> <i>confertiflorum</i>, <i>Hazardia</i> <i>squarrosa</i>, <i>Helianthus</i> <i>gracilentus</i>, <i>Hesperoyucca</i> <i>whipplei</i>, <i>Malacothamnus</i> <i>densiflorus</i>, <i>Prunus</i> <i>fremontii</i>, <i>Rhus</i> <i>ovata</i>, <i>Ribes</i> <i>quercetorum</i>, <i>Salvia</i> <i>apiana</i>, <i>Sambucus</i> <i>nigra</i>, <i>Senecio</i> <i>flaccidus</i> var. <i>douglasii</i>, <i>Toxicodendron</i> <i>diversilobum</i> and <i>Trichostema</i> <i>parishii</i>. Emergent trees may be present at low cover, including <i>Pinus</i> <i>sabiniana</i>, <i>Quercus</i> <i>douglasii</i> and <i>Quercus</i> <i>wislizeni</i> </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 3 m; canopy is open to intermittent and can be two tiered. Herbaceous layer is sparse to intermittent. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Dendromecon rigida</i> > 50% relative cover in the shrub canopy (Evens and San 2005, Keeler-Wolf and Evens 2006).</li>
		
		<li><i>Eriodictyon californicum</i> or <i>E. crassifolium</i>> 50% relative cover the shrub canopy with low to moderate cover (Klein et al. 2007, Ratchford et al. 2022a).</li>
		
		<li><i>Lotus scoparius</i> > 50% relative cover in the shrub canopy (Evens and San 2005, Keeler-Wolf and Evens 2006, Klein and Evens 2005, Ratchford et al. 2022a).</li>
		
		<li><i>Lupinus albifrons</i> > 50% relative cover in the shrub canopy (Keeler-Wolf et al. 2003b, Evens et al. 2006, Ratchford et al. 2022a).</li>
		
		<li><i>Eriodictyon californicum, Lotus scoparius, Pickeringia montana,</i> or <i>Lupinus albifrons</i> > 50% relative cover in the shrub canopy, or > 30% relative cover with other seral shrubs (Buck-Diaz et al. 2021, Sikes et al. 2021).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Lower to upper slopes and ridges, typically exposed, somewhat steep open settings. Areas often with recent disturbance, such as through clearing, fire, or intermittent flooding.  </div>
</div>

        
